{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744242251,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e35ffeiPmK0rQRK8nw1B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_50e675f01f4c47839becd024","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md","limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: sk-git\n3: description: \"Git workflow orchestrator OWNING all git/version-control intent: git worktree create/restructure (numbered wt/{NNNN}-{name} branches under .worktrees/), branch, conventional commits, pull request (PR), merge, rebase, finish work, integrate changes. Routes git-worktrees, git-commit, git-finish. NOT for spec folders / memory / save context (system-spec-kit) or code implementation / tests (sk-code).\"\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Bash, mcp__code_mode__call_tool_chain]\n5: argument-hint: \"[worktree|commit|finish]\"\n6: version: 1.1.3.0\n7: ---\n8: \n9: <!-- Keywords: git-workflow, git-worktree, create-worktree, numbered-worktree, restructure-worktrees, worktree-prefix, wt-branch, branch, commit, conventional-commits, pull-request, PR, merge, rebase, finish-work, integrate-changes, commit-hygiene, workspace-isolation, version-control, github, issues, pr-review, gitkraken, gitlens, gitlens-launchpad, gitlens-commit-composer, cross-platform-pr, multi-provider-issue -->\n10: <!-- Owns: git worktree / create worktree / numbered worktree / restructure worktrees / worktree prefix / wt/ branch / branch / commit / conventional commits / pull request / PR / merge / rebase / finish work / integrate changes / git workflow / gitkraken / gitlens / gitlens launchpad / gitlens commit composer / cross-platform pr / multi-provider issue. Does NOT own: spec folders, memory, continuity, save context (system-spec-kit); code implementation, tests (sk-code). -->\n11: \n12: # Git Workflows - Git Development Orchestrator\n13: \n14: Unified workflow guidance across workspace isolation, commit hygiene, and work completion.\n15: \n16: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\n17: \n18: ### When to Use This Orchestrator\n19: \n20: Use this orchestrator when:\n21: - Starting new git-based work\n22: - Unsure which git skill to use\n23: - Following complete git workflow (setup → work → complete)\n24: - Looking for git best practices (branch naming, commit conventions)\n25: \n26: ### When NOT to Use\n27: \n28: - Simple `git status` or `git log` queries (use Bash directly)\n29: - Non-git version control systems\n30: \n31: ### Keyword Triggers\n32: \n33: **Owned (route here):** `git worktree`, `worktree`, `create worktree`, `numbered worktree`, `restructure worktrees`, `worktree prefix`, `wt/ branch`, `branch`, `commit`, `conventional commits`, `pull request`, `pr`, `pr review`, `merge`, `rebase`, `finish work`, `integrate changes`, `git workflow`, `github`, `issue`, `gitkraken`, `gitlens`, `gitlens launchpad`, `commit composer`\n34: \n35: **Not owned (do NOT claim):** spec folders / memory / continuity / save context → `system-spec-kit`; code implementation / writing tests → `sk-code`. This skill commits and integrates that work; it does not author it.\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n40: \n41: \n42: ### Resource Loading Levels\n43: \n44: | Level       | When to Load             | Resources                  |\n45: | ----------- | ------------------------ | -------------------------- |\n46: | ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation   | Quick reference baseline   |\n47: | CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match  | Setup/commit/finish docs   |\n48: | ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request | Extended patterns/templates|\n49: \n50: ### Smart Router Pseudocode\n51: \n52: The authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, and ambiguity handling.\n53: \n54: ```python\n55: import re\n56: from pathlib import Path\n57: \n58: SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n59: RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\n60: DEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/quick_reference.md\"\n61: \n62: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n63:     \"WORKSPACE_SETUP\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"worktree\", \"create worktree\", \"numbered worktree\", \"restructure worktrees\", \"workspace\", \"parallel work\"]},\n64:     \"COMMIT\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"commit\", \"staged\", \"message\", \"conventional commit\"]},\n65:     \"FINISH\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"finish\", \"merge\", \"pr\", \"pull request\", \"integrate\"]},\n66:     \"GITKRAKEN_MCP\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"gitkraken\", \"gitlens\", \"launchpad\", \"commit composer\", \"cross-platform pr\", \"multi-provider issue\", \"gitlens start review\", \"gitlens start work\"]},\n67:     \"SHARED_PATTERNS\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"convention\", \"pattern\", \"reference\", \"branch naming\"]},\n68: }\n69: \n70: NOISY_SYNONYMS = {\n71:     \"WORKSPACE_SETUP\": {\"dirty workspace\": 2.2, \"unclean\": 1.4, \"mixed changes\": 1.5},\n72:     \"COMMIT\": {\"half-staged\": 2.0, \"boundary\": 1.4, \"split commit\": 1.4},\n73:     \"FINISH\": {\"ship\": 1.5, \"hotfix\": 1.6, \"trunk\": 1.8, \"minimal risk\": 1.4},\n74: }\n75: \n76: UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n77:     \"Confirm base branch (main/master/trunk)\",\n78:     \"Confirm whether staged/unstaged changes should be split\",\n79:     \"Provide required PR policy (squash, template fields, checks)\",\n80:     \"Confirm hotfix urgency versus cleanup tolerance\",\n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 583. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: sk-git\ndescription: \"Git workflow orchestrator OWNING all git/version-control intent: git worktree create/restructure (numbered wt/{NNNN}-{name} branches under .worktrees/), branch, conventional commits, pull request (PR), merge, rebase, finish work, integrate changes. Routes git-worktrees, git-commit, git-finish. NOT for spec folders / memory / save context (system-spec-kit) or code implementation / tests (sk-code).\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Bash, mcp__code_mode__call_tool_chain]\nargument-hint: \"[worktree|commit|finish]\"\nversion: 1.1.3.0\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: git-workflow, git-worktree, create-worktree, numbered-worktree, restructure-worktrees, worktree-prefix, wt-branch, branch, commit, conventional-commits, pull-request, PR, merge, rebase, finish-work, integrate-changes, commit-hygiene, workspace-isolation, version-control, github, issues, pr-review, gitkraken, gitlens, gitlens-launchpad, gitlens-commit-composer, cross-platform-pr, multi-provider-issue -->\n<!-- Owns: git worktree / create worktree / numbered worktree / restructure worktrees / worktree prefix / wt/ branch / branch / commit / conventional commits / pull request / PR / merge / rebase / finish work / integrate changes / git workflow / gitkraken / gitlens / gitlens launchpad / gitlens commit composer / cross-platform pr / multi-provider issue. Does NOT own: spec folders, memory, continuity, save context (system-spec-kit); code implementation, tests (sk-code). -->\n\n# Git Workflows - Git Development Orchestrator\n\nUnified workflow guidance across workspace isolation, commit hygiene, and work completion.\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### When to Use This Orchestrator\n\nUse this orchestrator when:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md","text":"---\nname: sk-git\ndescription: \"Git workflow orchestrator OWNING all git/version-control intent: git worktree create/restructure (numbered wt/{NNNN}-{name} branches under .worktrees/), branch, conventional commits, pull request (PR), merge, rebase, finish work, integrate changes. Routes git-worktrees, git-commit, git-finish. NOT for spec folders / memory / save context (system-spec-kit) or code implementation / tests (sk-code).\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Bash, mcp__code_mode__call_tool_chain]\nargument-hint: \"[worktree|commit|finish]\"\nversion: 1.1.3.0\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: git-workflow, git-worktree, create-worktree, numbered-worktree, restructure-worktrees, worktree-prefix, wt-branch, branch, commit, conventional-commits, pull-request, PR, merge, rebase, finish-work, integrate-changes, commit-hygiene, workspace-isolation, version-control, github, issues, pr-review, gitkraken, gitlens, gitlens-launchpad, gitlens-commit-composer, cross-platform-pr, multi-provider-issue -->\n<!-- Owns: git worktree / create worktree / numbered worktree / restructure worktrees / worktree prefix / wt/ branch / branch / commit / conventional commits / pull request / PR / merge / rebase / finish work / integrate changes / git workflow / gitkraken / gitlens / gitlens launchpad / gitlens commit composer / cross-platform pr / multi-provider issue. Does NOT own: spec folders, memory, continuity, save context (system-spec-kit); code implementation, tests (sk-code). -->\n\n# Git Workflows - Git Development Orchestrator\n\nUnified workflow guidance across workspace isolation, commit hygiene, and work completion.\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### When to Use This Orchestrator\n\nUse this orchestrator when:\n- Starting new git-based work\n- Unsure which git skill to use\n- Following complete git workflow (setup → work → complete)\n- Looking for git best practices (branch naming, commit conventions)\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- Simple `git status` or `git log` queries (use Bash directly)\n- Non-git version control systems\n\n### Keyword Triggers\n\n**Owned (route here):** `git worktree`, `worktree`, `create worktree`, `numbered worktree`, `restructure worktrees`, `worktree prefix`, `wt/ branch`, `branch`, `commit`, `conventional commits`, `pull request`, `pr`, `pr review`, `merge`, `rebase`, `finish work`, `integrate changes`, `git workflow`, `github`, `issue`, `gitkraken`, `gitlens`, `gitlens launchpad`, `commit composer`\n\n**Not owned (do NOT claim):** spec folders / memory / continuity / save context → `system-spec-kit`; code implementation / writing tests → `sk-code`. This skill commits and integrates that work; it does not author it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level       | When to Load             | Resources                  |\n| ----------- | ------------------------ | -------------------------- |\n| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation   | Quick reference baseline   |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match  | Setup/commit/finish docs   |\n| ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request | Extended patterns/templates|\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\nThe authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, and ambiguity handling.\n\n```python\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/quick_reference.md\"\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"WORKSPACE_SETUP\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"worktree\", \"create worktree\", \"numbered worktree\", \"restructure worktrees\", \"workspace\", \"parallel work\"]},\n    \"COMMIT\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"commit\", \"staged\", \"message\", \"conventional commit\"]},\n    \"FINISH\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"finish\", \"merge\", \"pr\", \"pull request\", \"integrate\"]},\n    \"GITKRAKEN_MCP\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"gitkraken\", \"gitlens\", \"launchpad\", \"commit composer\", \"cross-platform pr\", \"multi-provider issue\", \"gitlens start review\", \"gitlens start work\"]},\n    \"SHARED_PATTERNS\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"convention\", \"pattern\", \"reference\", \"branch naming\"]},\n}\n\nNOISY_SYNONYMS = {\n    \"WORKSPACE_SETUP\": {\"dirty workspace\": 2.2, \"unclean\": 1.4, \"mixed changes\": 1.5},\n    \"COMMIT\": {\"half-staged\": 2.0, \"boundary\": 1.4, \"split commit\": 1.4},\n    \"FINISH\": {\"ship\": 1.5, \"hotfix\": 1.6, \"trunk\": 1.8, \"minimal risk\": 1.4},\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm base branch (main/master/trunk)\",\n    \"Confirm whether staged/unstaged changes should be split\",\n    \"Provide required PR policy (squash, template fields, checks)\",\n    \"Confirm hotfix urgency versus cleanup tolerance\",","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":583,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1783744242244,"end":1783744242250}},"id":"prt_f4f712242001P4MJBdjdqYgwDk","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e35ffeiPmK0rQRK8nw1B","messageID":"msg_f4f71031a001rN8ebLkW4SEx3q"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744242253,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e35ffeiPmK0rQRK8nw1B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ea638cc017724f78a2c9b11a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n2: \"\"\"\n3: Comment hygiene checker — detects ephemeral-artifact pointers in code comment lines.\n4: \n5: Usage: check-comment-hygiene.sh <file>\n6: \n7: Exit codes:\n8:   0 — file is clean (no violations found)\n9:   1 — violations found (reported to stdout as FILEPATH:LINE: excerpt)\n10:   2 — file skipped (binary, unknown extension, or in excluded dir)\n11: \n12: Escape: add \"hygiene-ok\" anywhere on a comment line to suppress it.\n13: \n14: See: .opencode/skills/sk-code/shared/references/universal/code_style_guide.md §4\n15: \"\"\"\n16: import sys\n17: import os\n18: import re\n19: \n20: def main():\n21:     if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n22:         print(\"Usage: check-comment-hygiene.sh <file>\", file=sys.stderr)\n23:         sys.exit(2)\n24: \n25:     filepath = sys.argv[1]\n26: \n27:     # --- Excluded directories and file patterns ---\n28:     abs_path = os.path.abspath(filepath)\n29:     excluded_dirs = [\"/dist/\", \"/node_modules/\", \"/.git/\"]\n30:     for excl in excluded_dirs:\n31:         if excl in abs_path:\n32:             sys.exit(2)\n33: \n34:     basename = os.path.basename(filepath)\n35:     if basename.endswith(\".vitest.js\"):\n36:         sys.exit(2)\n37: \n38:     # --- Language detection from extension ---\n39:     _, ext = os.path.splitext(basename)\n40:     ext = ext.lower()\n41: \n42:     if ext in (\".ts\", \".tsx\", \".js\", \".mjs\", \".cjs\"):\n43:         lang = \"js\"\n44:     elif ext == \".py\":\n45:         lang = \"py\"\n46:     elif ext in (\".sh\", \".bash\"):\n47:         lang = \"sh\"\n48:     elif ext == \".jsonc\":\n49:         lang = \"jsonc\"\n50:     else:\n51:         # Unknown extension — skip silently\n52:         sys.exit(2)\n53: \n54:     # --- Read file ---\n55:     try:\n56:         with open(filepath, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\") as f:\n57:             lines = f.readlines()\n58:     except (OSError, IOError) as e:\n59:         print(f\"WARNING: cannot read {filepath}: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n60:         sys.exit(0)\n61: \n62:     # --- Comment detection ---\n63:     def find_unquoted_js_line_comment(line: str) -> int:\n64:         in_string = False\n65:         quote = \"\"\n66:         escaping = False\n67: \n68:         index = 0\n69:         while index < len(line):\n70:             char = line[index]\n71:             next_char = line[index + 1] if index + 1 < len(line) else \"\"\n72: \n73:             if in_string:\n74:                 if escaping:\n75:                     escaping = False\n76:                 elif char == \"\\\\\":\n77:                     escaping = True\n78:                 elif char == quote:\n79:                     in_string = False\n80:                 index += 1\n81:                 continue\n82: \n83:             if char in (\"'\", '\"', \"`\"):\n84:                 in_string = True\n85:                 quote = char\n86:                 index += 1\n87:                 continue\n88: \n89:             if char == \"/\" and next_char == \"/\":\n90:                 return index\n91: \n92:             index += 1\n93: \n94:         return -1\n95: \n96:     def find_unquoted_hash_comment(line: str) -> int:\n97:         in_string = False\n98:         quote = \"\"\n99:         escaping = False\n100: \n101:         for index, char in enumerate(line):\n102:             if in_string:\n103:                 if escaping:\n104:                     escaping = False\n105:                 elif char == \"\\\\\" and quote != \"'\":\n106:                     escaping = True\n107:                 elif char == quote:\n108:                     in_string = False\n109:                 continue\n110: \n111:             if char in (\"'\", '\"'):\n112:                 in_string = True\n113:                 quote = char\n114:                 continue\n115: \n116:             if char == \"#\" and (index == 0 or line[index - 1].isspace()):\n117:                 return index\n118: \n119:         return -1\n120: \n121:     def is_comment_line(stripped: str, lang: str) -> bool:\n122:         if lang in (\"js\", \"jsonc\"):\n123:             return stripped.startswith(\"//\") or stripped.startswith(\"*\") or stripped.startswith(\"/*\")\n124:         elif lang in (\"py\", \"sh\"):\n125:             return stripped.startswith(\"#\")\n126:         return False\n127: \n128:     def extract_comment_text(raw_line: str, lang: str) -> str:\n129:         stripped = raw_line.strip()\n130:         if is_comment_line(stripped, lang):\n131:             return stripped\n132: \n133:         if lang in (\"js\", \"jsonc\"):\n134:             comment_index = find_unquoted_js_line_comment(raw_line)\n135:             if comment_index >= 0:\n136:                 return raw_line[comment_index:].strip()\n137: \n138:         if lang in (\"py\", \"sh\"):\n139:             comment_index = find_unquoted_hash_comment(raw_line)\n140:             if comment_index >= 0:\n141:                 return raw_line[comment_index:].strip()\n142: \n143:         return \"\"\n144: \n145:     # --- Allowed-class patterns (these suppress violation detection) ---\n146:     # Order: check these BEFORE violation patterns.\n147:     ALLOWED_PATTERNS = [\n148:         re.compile(r'\\bCWE-\\d+\\b'),                    # CWE security codes\n149:         re.compile(r'\\bRFC\\s*-?\\d+\\b'),                 # RFC references\n150:         re.compile(r'\\bPOSIX\\b'),                        # POSIX standard\n151:         re.compile(r'\\bHTTP\\s+\\d{3}\\b'),                 # HTTP status codes\n152:         re.compile(r'\\bWEBFLOW\\s*:'),                   # WEBFLOW: platform tag\n153:         re.compile(r'\\bMOTION\\s*:'),                    # MOTION: platform tag\n154:         re.compile(r'\\bLENIS\\s*:'),                     # LENIS: platform tag\n155:         re.compile(r'\\bV\\d+\\s*:'),                       # V16: schema tag\n156:     ]\n157: \n158:     # --- Violation patterns ---\n159:     # Each is (pattern, description) for clear reporting.\n160:     # F-notation is intentionally excluded: repo comments use it heavily for function keys,\n161:     # figures, and field references, so genuine finding labels stay review-owned.\n162:     VIOLATION_PATTERNS = [\n163:         (re.compile(r'\\b\\d{3}/\\d{3}\\b'),                            \"packet/phase reference\"),\n164:         (re.compile(r'\\bRC-\\d+\\b'),                                  \"RC reference\"),\n165:         (re.compile(r'\\bADR-\\d+\\b'),                                \"ADR reference\"),\n166:         (re.compile(r'\\bREQ-\\d+\\b'),                                \"REQ reference\"),\n167:         (re.compile(r'\\bCHK-\\d+\\b'),                                \"CHK reference\"),\n168:         (re.compile(r'\\bT\\d{3,4}\\b'),                               \"task ID reference\"),\n169:         (re.compile(r'\\bpacket\\s+\\d+\\b', re.IGNORECASE),            \"packet number reference\"),\n170:         (re.compile(r'\\b\\d{3}\\s+packet\\b', re.IGNORECASE),          \"reversed packet number reference\"),\n171:         (re.compile(r'\\bphase[\\s-]\\d{3}\\b', re.IGNORECASE),          \"3-digit phase reference\"),\n172:         (re.compile(r'specs/[a-z0-9]+-[a-z0-9-]*/'),               \"spec path reference\"),\n173:         (re.compile(r'\\bWS-\\d+-\\d+\\b'),                             \"worktree session reference\"),\n174:         (re.compile(r'\\bDR-\\d+(?:-\\d+)?\\b'),                        \"deep review reference\"),\n175:         (re.compile(r'\\bP\\d+-Seat\\d+\\b'),                           \"council seat reference\"),\n176:         (re.compile(r'\\breview\\s+finding\\b', re.IGNORECASE),        \"review finding reference\"),\n177:         (re.compile(r'\\bchecklist\\s+item\\s+\\d+\\b', re.IGNORECASE), \"checklist item reference\"),\n178:         (re.compile(r'\\b[Pp]\\d-finding[-\\s]\\d+\\b'),                 \"finding id reference\"),\n179:         (re.compile(r'\\bfinding\\s+#\\d+\\b', re.IGNORECASE),         \"finding id reference\"),\n180:     ]\n181: \n182:     violations = []\n183: \n184:     for lineno, raw_line in enumerate(lines, start=1):\n185:         comment_text = extract_comment_text(raw_line, lang)\n186: \n187:         if not comment_text:\n188:             continue\n189: \n190:         # Hygiene-ok escape: skip this line entirely\n191:         if \"hygiene-ok\" in comment_text:\n192:             continue\n193: \n194:         # Check allowed-class patterns first — if any match, skip violation check\n195:         if any(pat.search(comment_text) for pat in ALLOWED_PATTERNS):\n196:             continue\n197: \n198:         # Check violation patterns\n199:         for vpat, _desc in VIOLATION_PATTERNS:\n200:             m = vpat.search(comment_text)\n201:             if m:\n202:                 excerpt = raw_line.rstrip()\n203:                 violations.append(f\"{filepath}:{lineno}: {excerpt}\")\n204:                 break  # One violation per line is enough\n205: \n206:     if violations:\n207:         for v in violations:\n208:             print(v)\n209:         sys.exit(1)\n210: \n211:     sys.exit(0)\n212: \n213: \n214: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n215:     main()\n\n(End of file - total 215 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nComment hygiene checker — detects ephemeral-artifact pointers in code comment lines.\n\nUsage: check-comment-hygiene.sh <file>\n\nExit codes:\n  0 — file is clean (no violations found)\n  1 — violations found (reported to stdout as FILEPATH:LINE: excerpt)\n  2 — file skipped (binary, unknown extension, or in excluded dir)\n\nEscape: add \"hygiene-ok\" anywhere on a comment line to suppress it.\n\nSee: .opencode/skills/sk-code/shared/references/universal/code_style_guide.md §4\n\"\"\"\nimport sys\nimport os\nimport re\n\ndef main():","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nComment hygiene checker — detects ephemeral-artifact pointers in code comment lines.\n\nUsage: check-comment-hygiene.sh <file>\n\nExit codes:\n  0 — file is clean (no violations found)\n  1 — violations found (reported to stdout as FILEPATH:LINE: excerpt)\n  2 — file skipped (binary, unknown extension, or in excluded dir)\n\nEscape: add \"hygiene-ok\" anywhere on a comment line to suppress it.\n\nSee: .opencode/skills/sk-code/shared/references/universal/code_style_guide.md §4\n\"\"\"\nimport sys\nimport os\nimport re\n\ndef main():\n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        print(\"Usage: check-comment-hygiene.sh <file>\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(2)\n\n    filepath = sys.argv[1]\n\n    # --- Excluded directories and file patterns ---\n    abs_path = os.path.abspath(filepath)\n    excluded_dirs = [\"/dist/\", \"/node_modules/\", \"/.git/\"]\n    for excl in excluded_dirs:\n        if excl in abs_path:\n            sys.exit(2)\n\n    basename = os.path.basename(filepath)\n    if basename.endswith(\".vitest.js\"):\n        sys.exit(2)\n\n    # --- Language detection from extension ---\n    _, ext = os.path.splitext(basename)\n    ext = ext.lower()\n\n    if ext in (\".ts\", \".tsx\", \".js\", \".mjs\", \".cjs\"):\n        lang = \"js\"\n    elif ext == \".py\":\n        lang = \"py\"\n    elif ext in (\".sh\", \".bash\"):\n        lang = \"sh\"\n    elif ext == \".jsonc\":\n        lang = \"jsonc\"\n    else:\n        # Unknown extension — skip silently\n        sys.exit(2)\n\n    # --- Read file ---\n    try:\n        with open(filepath, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\") as f:\n            lines = f.readlines()\n    except (OSError, IOError) as e:\n        print(f\"WARNING: cannot read {filepath}: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(0)\n\n    # --- Comment detection ---\n    def find_unquoted_js_line_comment(line: str) -> int:\n        in_string = False\n        quote = \"\"\n        escaping = False\n\n        index = 0\n        while index < len(line):\n            char = line[index]\n            next_char = line[index + 1] if index + 1 < len(line) else \"\"\n\n            if in_string:\n                if escaping:\n                    escaping = False\n                elif char == \"\\\\\":\n                    escaping = True\n                elif char == quote:\n                    in_string = False\n                index += 1\n                continue\n\n            if char in (\"'\", '\"', \"`\"):\n                in_string = True\n                quote = char\n                index += 1\n                continue\n\n            if char == \"/\" and next_char == \"/\":\n                return index\n\n            index += 1\n\n        return -1\n\n    def find_unquoted_hash_comment(line: str) -> int:\n        in_string = False\n        quote = \"\"\n        escaping = False\n\n        for index, char in enumerate(line):\n            if in_string:\n                if escaping:\n                    escaping = False\n                elif char == \"\\\\\" and quote != \"'\":\n                    escaping = True\n                elif char == quote:\n                    in_string = False\n                continue\n\n            if char in (\"'\", '\"'):\n                in_string = True\n                quote = char\n                continue\n\n            if char == \"#\" and (index == 0 or line[index - 1].isspace()):\n                return index\n\n        return -1\n\n    def is_comment_line(stripped: str, lang: str) -> bool:\n        if lang in (\"js\", \"jsonc\"):\n            return stripped.startswith(\"//\") or stripped.startswith(\"*\") or stripped.startswith(\"/*\")\n        elif lang in (\"py\", \"sh\"):\n            return stripped.startswith(\"#\")\n        return False\n\n    def extract_comment_text(raw_line: str, lang: str) -> str:\n        stripped = raw_line.strip()\n        if is_comment_line(stripped, lang):\n            return stripped\n\n        if lang in (\"js\", \"jsonc\"):\n            comment_index = find_unquoted_js_line_comment(raw_line)\n            if comment_index >= 0:\n                return raw_line[comment_index:].strip()\n\n        if lang in (\"py\", \"sh\"):\n            comment_index = find_unquoted_hash_comment(raw_line)\n            if comment_index >= 0:\n                return raw_line[comment_index:].strip()\n\n        return \"\"\n\n    # --- Allowed-class patterns (these suppress violation detection) ---\n    # Order: check these BEFORE violation patterns.\n    ALLOWED_PATTERNS = [\n        re.compile(r'\\bCWE-\\d+\\b'),                    # CWE security codes\n        re.compile(r'\\bRFC\\s*-?\\d+\\b'),                 # RFC references\n        re.compile(r'\\bPOSIX\\b'),                        # POSIX standard\n        re.compile(r'\\bHTTP\\s+\\d{3}\\b'),                 # HTTP status codes\n        re.compile(r'\\bWEBFLOW\\s*:'),                   # WEBFLOW: platform tag\n        re.compile(r'\\bMOTION\\s*:'),                    # MOTION: platform tag\n        re.compile(r'\\bLENIS\\s*:'),                     # LENIS: platform tag\n        re.compile(r'\\bV\\d+\\s*:'),                       # V16: schema tag\n    ]\n\n    # --- Violation patterns ---\n    # Each is (pattern, description) for clear reporting.\n    # F-notation is intentionally excluded: repo comments use it heavily for function keys,\n    # figures, and field references, so genuine finding labels stay review-owned.\n    VIOLATION_PATTERNS = [\n        (re.compile(r'\\b\\d{3}/\\d{3}\\b'),                            \"packet/phase reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bRC-\\d+\\b'),                                  \"RC reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bADR-\\d+\\b'),                                \"ADR reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bREQ-\\d+\\b'),                                \"REQ reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bCHK-\\d+\\b'),                                \"CHK reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bT\\d{3,4}\\b'),                               \"task ID reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bpacket\\s+\\d+\\b', re.IGNORECASE),            \"packet number reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\b\\d{3}\\s+packet\\b', re.IGNORECASE),          \"reversed packet number reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bphase[\\s-]\\d{3}\\b', re.IGNORECASE),          \"3-digit phase reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'specs/[a-z0-9]+-[a-z0-9-]*/'),               \"spec path reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bWS-\\d+-\\d+\\b'),                             \"worktree session reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bDR-\\d+(?:-\\d+)?\\b'),                        \"deep review reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bP\\d+-Seat\\d+\\b'),                           \"council seat reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\breview\\s+finding\\b', re.IGNORECASE),        \"review finding reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bchecklist\\s+item\\s+\\d+\\b', re.IGNORECASE), \"checklist item reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\b[Pp]\\d-finding[-\\s]\\d+\\b'),                 \"finding id reference\"),\n        (re.compile(r'\\bfinding\\s+#\\d+\\b', re.IGNORECASE),         \"finding id reference\"),\n    ]\n\n    violations = []\n\n    for lineno, raw_line in enumerate(lines, start=1):\n        comment_text = extract_comment_text(raw_line, lang)\n\n        if not comment_text:\n            continue\n\n        # Hygiene-ok escape: skip this line entirely\n        if \"hygiene-ok\" in comment_text:\n            continue\n\n        # Check allowed-class patterns first — if any match, skip violation check\n        if any(pat.search(comment_text) for pat in ALLOWED_PATTERNS):\n            continue\n\n        # Check violation patterns\n        for vpat, _desc in VIOLATION_PATTERNS:\n            m = vpat.search(comment_text)\n            if m:\n                excerpt = raw_line.rstrip()\n                violations.append(f\"{filepath}:{lineno}: {excerpt}\")\n                break  # One violation per line is enough\n\n    if violations:\n        for v in violations:\n            print(v)\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    sys.exit(0)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":215,"totalLines":215,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh","time":{"start":1783744242241,"end":1783744242253}},"id":"prt_f4f71223f0016Y3vySDuiLv2Gn","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e35ffeiPmK0rQRK8nw1B","messageID":"msg_f4f71031a001rN8ebLkW4SEx3q"}}
