{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744384370,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e35ffeiPmK0rQRK8nw1B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_51cd68f087e74fe4b050b7de","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md","limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: mcp-code-mode\n3: description: \"MCP orchestration via TypeScript execution. Use Code Mode for ALL external MCP tool calls; ~98% context reduction, type-safe.\"\n4: allowed-tools: [mcp__code_mode__call_tool_chain, mcp__code_mode__list_tools, mcp__code_mode__search_tools, mcp__code_mode__tool_info]\n5: version: 1.0.8.0\n6: ---\n7: \n8: <!-- Keywords: mcp-code-mode, typescript-execution, multi-tool-workflow, tool-orchestration, context-reduction, progressive-discovery, external-api-integration, mcp-server -->\n9: \n10: # MCP Code Mode\n11: \n12: Execute TypeScript code with direct access to 200+ MCP tools through progressive disclosure. Code Mode eliminates context overhead by loading tools on-demand, enabling complex multi-tool workflows in a single execution with state persistence and built-in error handling.\n13: \n14: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\n15: \n16: ### Use Code Mode When\n17: \n18: **MANDATORY for ALL MCP tool calls**:\n19: - ✅ Calling ClickUp, Notion, Figma, MyService, Chrome DevTools, or any other MCP tools\n20: - ✅ Accessing external APIs through MCP servers\n21: - ✅ Managing tasks in project management tools\n22: - ✅ Interacting with design tools, databases, or services\n23: - ✅ Browser automation and web interactions\n24: \n25: **Benefits over traditional tool calling**:\n26: - 🚀 **98.7% context reduction** - 1.6k tokens vs 141k for 47 tools\n27: - ⚡ **60% faster execution** - Single execution vs 15+ API round trips\n28: - 🔗 **State persistence** - Data flows naturally between operations\n29: - 🛡️ **Type safety** - Full TypeScript support with autocomplete\n30: - 🎯 **Progressive loading** - Tools discovered on-demand, zero upfront cost\n31: \n32: ### Do NOT Use Code Mode For\n33: \n34: **Use native tools instead**:\n35: - ❌ File operations (use Read, Write, Edit tools)\n36: - ❌ Text searching (use Grep tool)\n37: - ❌ File discovery (use Glob tool)\n38: - ❌ Bash commands (use Bash tool)\n39: - ❌ Continuity recovery (use `/speckit:resume` first; only use native Spec Kit Memory tools after `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs` has been exhausted)\n40: - ❌ Sequential Thinking (call `sequential_thinking_sequentialthinking()` directly - **NATIVE MCP**)\n41: \n42: > See Section 4 for details on Native MCP vs Code Mode distinction.\n43: \n44: ### Common Use Cases\n45: \n46: | Scenario                     | Code Mode Approach                                                      | Benefit                     |\n47: | ---------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------- |\n48: | **Create ClickUp task**      | `call_tool_chain({ code: \"await clickup.clickup_create_task({...})\" })` | Type-safe, single execution |\n49: | **Multi-tool workflow**      | Figma → ClickUp → MyService in one execution                              | State persists, 5× faster   |\n50: | **Browser automation**       | Chrome DevTools MCP for testing/screenshots                             | Sandboxed, reliable         |\n51: | **Design-to-implementation** | Fetch Figma design → Create task → Update CMS                           | Atomic workflow             |\n52: | **External API access**      | Any MCP server (Notion, GitHub, etc.)                                   | Progressive tool loading    |\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n57: \n58: \n59: ### Resource Loading Levels\n60: \n\n(Showing lines 1-60 of 479. Use offset=61 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: mcp-code-mode\ndescription: \"MCP orchestration via TypeScript execution. Use Code Mode for ALL external MCP tool calls; ~98% context reduction, type-safe.\"\nallowed-tools: [mcp__code_mode__call_tool_chain, mcp__code_mode__list_tools, mcp__code_mode__search_tools, mcp__code_mode__tool_info]\nversion: 1.0.8.0\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: mcp-code-mode, typescript-execution, multi-tool-workflow, tool-orchestration, context-reduction, progressive-discovery, external-api-integration, mcp-server -->\n\n# MCP Code Mode\n\nExecute TypeScript code with direct access to 200+ MCP tools through progressive disclosure. Code Mode eliminates context overhead by loading tools on-demand, enabling complex multi-tool workflows in a single execution with state persistence and built-in error handling.\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### Use Code Mode When\n\n**MANDATORY for ALL MCP tool calls**:\n- ✅ Calling ClickUp, Notion, Figma, MyService, Chrome DevTools, or any other MCP tools\n- ✅ Accessing external APIs through MCP servers","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md","text":"---\nname: mcp-code-mode\ndescription: \"MCP orchestration via TypeScript execution. Use Code Mode for ALL external MCP tool calls; ~98% context reduction, type-safe.\"\nallowed-tools: [mcp__code_mode__call_tool_chain, mcp__code_mode__list_tools, mcp__code_mode__search_tools, mcp__code_mode__tool_info]\nversion: 1.0.8.0\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: mcp-code-mode, typescript-execution, multi-tool-workflow, tool-orchestration, context-reduction, progressive-discovery, external-api-integration, mcp-server -->\n\n# MCP Code Mode\n\nExecute TypeScript code with direct access to 200+ MCP tools through progressive disclosure. Code Mode eliminates context overhead by loading tools on-demand, enabling complex multi-tool workflows in a single execution with state persistence and built-in error handling.\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### Use Code Mode When\n\n**MANDATORY for ALL MCP tool calls**:\n- ✅ Calling ClickUp, Notion, Figma, MyService, Chrome DevTools, or any other MCP tools\n- ✅ Accessing external APIs through MCP servers\n- ✅ Managing tasks in project management tools\n- ✅ Interacting with design tools, databases, or services\n- ✅ Browser automation and web interactions\n\n**Benefits over traditional tool calling**:\n- 🚀 **98.7% context reduction** - 1.6k tokens vs 141k for 47 tools\n- ⚡ **60% faster execution** - Single execution vs 15+ API round trips\n- 🔗 **State persistence** - Data flows naturally between operations\n- 🛡️ **Type safety** - Full TypeScript support with autocomplete\n- 🎯 **Progressive loading** - Tools discovered on-demand, zero upfront cost\n\n### Do NOT Use Code Mode For\n\n**Use native tools instead**:\n- ❌ File operations (use Read, Write, Edit tools)\n- ❌ Text searching (use Grep tool)\n- ❌ File discovery (use Glob tool)\n- ❌ Bash commands (use Bash tool)\n- ❌ Continuity recovery (use `/speckit:resume` first; only use native Spec Kit Memory tools after `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs` has been exhausted)\n- ❌ Sequential Thinking (call `sequential_thinking_sequentialthinking()` directly - **NATIVE MCP**)\n\n> See Section 4 for details on Native MCP vs Code Mode distinction.\n\n### Common Use Cases\n\n| Scenario                     | Code Mode Approach                                                      | Benefit                     |\n| ---------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------- |\n| **Create ClickUp task**      | `call_tool_chain({ code: \"await clickup.clickup_create_task({...})\" })` | Type-safe, single execution |\n| **Multi-tool workflow**      | Figma → ClickUp → MyService in one execution                              | State persists, 5× faster   |\n| **Browser automation**       | Chrome DevTools MCP for testing/screenshots                             | Sandboxed, reliable         |\n| **Design-to-implementation** | Fetch Figma design → Create task → Update CMS                           | Atomic workflow             |\n| **External API access**      | Any MCP server (Notion, GitHub, etc.)                                   | Progressive tool loading    |\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":60,"totalLines":479,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1783744384365,"end":1783744384369}},"id":"prt_f4f734d6c001z0DqRE9Ur6BKDy","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e35ffeiPmK0rQRK8nw1B","messageID":"msg_f4f7329c7001tUCw0qLWNeZN9S"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744384372,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e35ffeiPmK0rQRK8nw1B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_aa27ac6055b54f4eb2c3c278","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/scripts/hooks/dispatch-preflight-lint.mjs","limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/scripts/hooks/dispatch-preflight-lint.mjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: // PreToolUse(Bash) preflight for CLI dispatch.\n3: //\n4: // Intercepts a composed `opencode run` / `claude -p` command BEFORE it spawns and evaluates the\n5: // target skill's declared hard_rules (SKILL.md `hard_rules:` frontmatter). A `block`-severity\n6: // violation denies the call with the rule's reason; `warn` violations attach an advisory and let\n7: // the normal permission flow proceed. Runs on every Bash call, so it fast-exits on anything that\n8: // is not a dispatch shape, and it FAILS OPEN — any internal error approves silently, never blocks.\n9: \n10: import { readHardRules, evaluate } from '../lib/dispatch-rule-checks.mjs';\n11: import path from 'node:path';\n12: \n13: // Dispatch-shape registry: command pattern → the skill whose SKILL.md declares its hard_rules.\n14: // `skill` is the short display name (used in advisory/block messages); `packetPath` is the\n15: // hub-relative path segment under .opencode/skills/ used to resolve SKILL.md — both\n16: // cli-opencode and cli-claude-code now live nested under the cli-external parent hub,\n17: // so packetPath carries the hub prefix while skill stays\n18: // the short, human-readable name. Extend by adding an entry as new cli-* dispatch skills\n19: // gain a hard_rules block.\n20: const DISPATCH_SKILLS = [\n21:   { test: /\\bopencode\\s+run\\b/, skill: 'cli-opencode', packetPath: 'cli-external/cli-opencode' },\n22:   { test: /\\bclaude\\s+(-p|--print)\\b/, skill: 'cli-claude-code', packetPath: 'cli-external/cli-claude-code' },\n23: ];\n24: \n25: function approve() {\n26:   // No output + exit 0 → defer to the normal permission flow.\n27:   process.exit(0);\n28: }\n29: \n30: async function readStdin() {\n31:   const chunks = [];\n32:   for await (const chunk of process.stdin) chunks.push(chunk);\n33:   return Buffer.concat(chunks).toString('utf8');\n34: }\n35: \n36: async function main() {\n37:   let payload;\n38:   try {\n39:     payload = JSON.parse(await readStdin());\n40:   } catch {\n41:     return approve(); // no/invalid payload → fail open\n42:   }\n43: \n44:   if (payload?.tool_name !== 'Bash') return approve();\n45:   const command = payload?.tool_input?.command;\n46:   if (typeof command !== 'string' || command.length === 0) return approve();\n47: \n48:   // Fast-exit unless the command is a known dispatch shape.\n49:   const match = DISPATCH_SKILLS.find((d) => d.test.test(command));\n50:   if (!match) return approve();\n51: \n52:   const projectDir = process.env.CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR || process.cwd();\n53:   const skillMd = path.join(projectDir, '.opencode', 'skills', match.packetPath, 'SKILL.md');\n54:   const rules = readHardRules(skillMd);\n55:   if (rules.length === 0) return approve(); // nothing declared → nothing to enforce\n56: \n57:   const violations = evaluate(command, rules);\n58:   if (violations.length === 0) return approve();\n59: \n60:   const blocking = violations.filter((v) => v.severity === 'block');\n61:   const warnings = violations.filter((v) => v.severity === 'warn');\n62: \n63:   if (blocking.length > 0) {\n64:     const reason = `Dispatch blocked by ${match.skill} hard-rule(s):\\n` +\n65:       blocking.map((v) => `  • [${v.id}] ${v.message}`).join('\\n');\n66:     process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify({\n67:       hookSpecificOutput: {\n68:         hookEventName: 'PreToolUse',\n69:         permissionDecision: 'deny',\n70:         permissionDecisionReason: reason,\n71:       },\n72:     }));\n73:     return process.exit(0);\n74:   }\n75: \n76:   // Warn-only: surface the advisory without overriding the permission decision.\n77:   const advisory = `⚠ ${match.skill} dispatch hard-rule advisory:\\n` +\n78:     warnings.map((v) => `  • [${v.id}] ${v.message}`).join('\\n');\n79:   process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify({\n80:     hookSpecificOutput: { hookEventName: 'PreToolUse', additionalContext: advisory },\n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 85. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// PreToolUse(Bash) preflight for CLI dispatch.\n//\n// Intercepts a composed `opencode run` / `claude -p` command BEFORE it spawns and evaluates the\n// target skill's declared hard_rules (SKILL.md `hard_rules:` frontmatter). A `block`-severity\n// violation denies the call with the rule's reason; `warn` violations attach an advisory and let\n// the normal permission flow proceed. Runs on every Bash call, so it fast-exits on anything that\n// is not a dispatch shape, and it FAILS OPEN — any internal error approves silently, never blocks.\n\nimport { readHardRules, evaluate } from '../lib/dispatch-rule-checks.mjs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\n\n// Dispatch-shape registry: command pattern → the skill whose SKILL.md declares its hard_rules.\n// `skill` is the short display name (used in advisory/block messages); `packetPath` is the\n// hub-relative path segment under .opencode/skills/ used to resolve SKILL.md — both\n// cli-opencode and cli-claude-code now live nested under the cli-external parent hub,\n// so packetPath carries the hub prefix while skill stays\n// the short, human-readable name. Extend by adding an entry as new cli-* dispatch skills\n// gain a hard_rules block.\nconst DISPATCH_SKILLS = [","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/scripts/hooks/dispatch-preflight-lint.mjs","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// PreToolUse(Bash) preflight for CLI dispatch.\n//\n// Intercepts a composed `opencode run` / `claude -p` command BEFORE it spawns and evaluates the\n// target skill's declared hard_rules (SKILL.md `hard_rules:` frontmatter). A `block`-severity\n// violation denies the call with the rule's reason; `warn` violations attach an advisory and let\n// the normal permission flow proceed. Runs on every Bash call, so it fast-exits on anything that\n// is not a dispatch shape, and it FAILS OPEN — any internal error approves silently, never blocks.\n\nimport { readHardRules, evaluate } from '../lib/dispatch-rule-checks.mjs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\n\n// Dispatch-shape registry: command pattern → the skill whose SKILL.md declares its hard_rules.\n// `skill` is the short display name (used in advisory/block messages); `packetPath` is the\n// hub-relative path segment under .opencode/skills/ used to resolve SKILL.md — both\n// cli-opencode and cli-claude-code now live nested under the cli-external parent hub,\n// so packetPath carries the hub prefix while skill stays\n// the short, human-readable name. Extend by adding an entry as new cli-* dispatch skills\n// gain a hard_rules block.\nconst DISPATCH_SKILLS = [\n  { test: /\\bopencode\\s+run\\b/, skill: 'cli-opencode', packetPath: 'cli-external/cli-opencode' },\n  { test: /\\bclaude\\s+(-p|--print)\\b/, skill: 'cli-claude-code', packetPath: 'cli-external/cli-claude-code' },\n];\n\nfunction approve() {\n  // No output + exit 0 → defer to the normal permission flow.\n  process.exit(0);\n}\n\nasync function readStdin() {\n  const chunks = [];\n  for await (const chunk of process.stdin) chunks.push(chunk);\n  return Buffer.concat(chunks).toString('utf8');\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  let payload;\n  try {\n    payload = JSON.parse(await readStdin());\n  } catch {\n    return approve(); // no/invalid payload → fail open\n  }\n\n  if (payload?.tool_name !== 'Bash') return approve();\n  const command = payload?.tool_input?.command;\n  if (typeof command !== 'string' || command.length === 0) return approve();\n\n  // Fast-exit unless the command is a known dispatch shape.\n  const match = DISPATCH_SKILLS.find((d) => d.test.test(command));\n  if (!match) return approve();\n\n  const projectDir = process.env.CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR || process.cwd();\n  const skillMd = path.join(projectDir, '.opencode', 'skills', match.packetPath, 'SKILL.md');\n  const rules = readHardRules(skillMd);\n  if (rules.length === 0) return approve(); // nothing declared → nothing to enforce\n\n  const violations = evaluate(command, rules);\n  if (violations.length === 0) return approve();\n\n  const blocking = violations.filter((v) => v.severity === 'block');\n  const warnings = violations.filter((v) => v.severity === 'warn');\n\n  if (blocking.length > 0) {\n    const reason = `Dispatch blocked by ${match.skill} hard-rule(s):\\n` +\n      blocking.map((v) => `  • [${v.id}] ${v.message}`).join('\\n');\n    process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify({\n      hookSpecificOutput: {\n        hookEventName: 'PreToolUse',\n        permissionDecision: 'deny',\n        permissionDecisionReason: reason,\n      },\n    }));\n    return process.exit(0);\n  }\n\n  // Warn-only: surface the advisory without overriding the permission decision.\n  const advisory = `⚠ ${match.skill} dispatch hard-rule advisory:\\n` +\n    warnings.map((v) => `  • [${v.id}] ${v.message}`).join('\\n');\n  process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify({\n    hookSpecificOutput: { hookEventName: 'PreToolUse', additionalContext: advisory },","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":85,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/scripts/hooks/dispatch-preflight-lint.mjs","time":{"start":1783744384364,"end":1783744384371}},"id":"prt_f4f734d6a001b7HcZUnnpLmzHf","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e35ffeiPmK0rQRK8nw1B","messageID":"msg_f4f7329c7001tUCw0qLWNeZN9S"}}
